<P>
   MISSION -A veteran copper miner and his family told federal
regulators for months about unsafe conditions at an underground
mine near Tucson, but the complaints were ignored and the miner
died in a rock-fall this year. An (beginitalic)Arizona Republic
(enditalic)investigation, based on interviews with miners, union
officials, regulators and documents obtained through state and
federal public records requests, found that federal inspectors
repeatedly failed to follow up on complaints of dangerous
conditions at Asarco Inc.'s Mission Mine. Story will move in the
``A'' category.
