   POWER -It was supposed to deliver lower electric rates and a
stable source of power. But for Californians, electricity
deregulation has brought soaring power bills and rolling blackouts.
It's a situation not unlike Arizona's, where, due to unprecedented
growth and limited resources, utilities such as Arizona Public
Service Co. and Salt River Project must now increasingly import
electricity to meet demand. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   GOP -For all that went right for the Republicans last week,
history says it's too early to take comfort in polls, which now
give Texas Gov. George W. Bush a double-digit lead over the
presumptive Democratic presidential nominee, Vice President Al
Gore. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
