<HEADLINE>
BOND CALENDAR 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The word PLUS in parentheses has been used instead of the
symbol, which is nontransmittable to many newspaper systems.) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financing this week includes Monday's
regular weekly auction of new three- and six-month bills and the
Treasury's quarterly refunding, including five- and 10-year notes
and a 30-year bond. The refunding begins Tuesday with the sale of
$10 billion of five-year notes, followed by $10 billion of 10-year
notes on Wednesday and $5 billion of 30-year bonds on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   At the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 6.03 percent
and on the six-month issue 6.02 percent. In when-issued trading,
the five-year note was offered at a price to yield 6.00 percent,
the 10-year note at 5.78 percent and the 30-year bond at 5.76
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
