   FILMCREW-DEATHS (Los Angeles) _ The electrocution of a grip on
the set of TV's ``The X-Files'' is one of hundreds of similar
accidents that occur every year in Hollywood's quest for realistic
movie thrills. Some insiders see the fatal incident as a wake-up
call for an industry too accustomed to taking risks to draw
audiences. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
