<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGNOTE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROTATION' REVOLVING DOOR OPENS FOR EX-WAVE WISE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND _ Matt Wise will become the 12th pitcher to start a
game for the Anaheim Angels when he faces the Red Sox at Edison
Field on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Wise's opportunity, as for many of the others, has come as a
result of injuries to other starters. Wise, who went to Bonita
High, Pepperdine and Cal State Fullerton, is getting his chance
because Seth Etherton has tendinitis in his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Wise went 9-6 with a 3.69 ERA, two complete games and one
shutout in 19 starts for Triple-A Edmonton this season. He was
called up Wednesday when reliever Al Levine got hurt. And after a
few days in the bullpen, he learned he'd be making his first
major-league start this week.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a surprise, ever since I was called up,'' said Wise,
who is 6-foot-4, 190 pounds. ``When they told me I was starting
Wednesday, it caught me off guard. But I'm looking forward to it.''
</P>
<P>
   Wise, who lives in LaVerne, was part of a rotation at Double-A
Erie last season that included Etherton, Ramon Ortiz and Brian
Cooper. They made it to the big leagues without him, but he says he
understands.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had a lot of stuff to work on,'' he said. ``Plus, I had
(elbow) surgery last year. I wanted to take advantage of the
opportunity to pitch there (Edmonton). I was happy for those guys.
But I wanted to make sure I was ready before I came up here. I
still have things to work on, but I feel I'm close enough to do
good.''
</P>
<P>
   __ No payback: Scioscia defended his players' decision not to
retaliate against the Indians' Manny Ramirez for a spikes-high
slide into catcher Matt Walbeck on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez's spikes cut Walbeck's thigh, and the Angels thought the
play was dirty. But when Ramirez batted again one inning later with
first base open and two outs, pitcher Scott Schoeneweis didn't
brush back Ramirez.
</P>
<P>
   ``We play the game hard and we play the game clean,'' Scioscia
said. They got the message we weren't happy with the slide.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's the first time we've seen something like that with
(Ramirez). It would be different if a player habitually does it.
And even so, it doesn't necessarily mean we'd put a ball in his
neck. There are different ways of handling things. Messages can be
sent in different forms.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Washburn activated: Pitcher Jarrod Washburn will be activated
today and start against the Red Sox at Edison Field. Washburn (6-2,
3.87 ERA) has been on the disabled list since July 22 with a sore
left biceps.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels will have to make room for Washburn on the roster and
are expected to demote reserve outfielder Edgard Clemente. Clemente
is out of options and would have to clear waivers before being
assigned to the minors. There is a good chance another team would
claim him.
</P>
</TEXT>
